@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>At PropertyApp, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how it is used, and the steps we take to ensure its security.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>When you use PropertyApp, we may collect the following types of information:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> This includes your name, email address, contact details, and any other personal details provided during registration, profile setup, or property listings.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We collect data on how you interact with our website, including IP address, browser type, pages visited, and the time and date of visits. This information helps us improve user experience.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
    <li>To provide and maintain our services, including user account management and property listings.</li>
    <li>To send notifications related to your account, property inquiries, and responses to customer service requests.</li>
    <li>To analyze and improve our services, ensuring PropertyApp meets your needs.</li>
    <li>To personalize content and recommend properties based on your preferences.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
<p>We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your data in the following situations:</p>
<ul>
    <li>With service providers who assist us in operating the app (such as hosting, payment processing, and analytics) and who are bound by confidentiality agreements.</li>
    <li>When required by law or to protect the rights and safety of PropertyApp, its users, or the public.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Security</h2>
<p>We implement security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, and disclosure. However, no online service is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security. We encourage users to use strong passwords and safeguard their login credentials.</p>

<h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
<p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request access to the personal information we hold about you.</li>
    <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
    <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request the deletion of your personal data, subject to legal and operational obligations.</li>
    <li><strong>Objection and Restriction:</strong> You may object to or request a restriction on data processing in certain cases.</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [your email or support contact].</p>

<h2>6. Cookies</h2>
<p>We use cookies to improve the functionality of our site and enhance user experience. You may manage or disable cookies through your browser settings, though some site features may be affected.</p>

<h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We encourage you to review this policy regularly. Any significant updates will be communicated via email or site notifications.</p>

<h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@propertyapp.com">support@propertyapp.com</a>.</p>
